 ─── THE DETECTOR WARS ─────────────────────────────────────────────

 "how does Pangram work?" made the rounds on lobste.rs this week.
 short version: AI-text detectors are themselves neural nets trained
 to smell other neural nets. it's narcs all the way down.

 the arms race is pure 90s: crackers vs copy protection, now
 generators vs detectors. every watermark gets stripped, every
 detector gets fooled, every fooling gets detected. sustainable
 employment for everyone. the scene provides.

 ─── "REVIEWING AI CODE IS NOT A VIABLE ARGUMENT" ──────────────────

 hot take with 11 upvotes and a hundred silent nods: if your safety
 story for machine-generated code is "a human will review it", you
 don't have a safety story, you have a scapegoat with a login.

 reviewers rubber-stamp 400-line diffs from HUMANS already. the
 fix isn't heroic review, it's the boring stuff: tests, types,
 sandboxes, small diffs. same as it ever was.

 ─── REWRITE SCENE REPORT ──────────────────────────────────────────

 roc-lang crew posted "how our rust-to-zig rewrite is going" and
 pulled 183 points, which in lobste.rs currency is a platinum
 record. groups used to port demos amiga -> pc for glory; now they
 port compilers rust -> zig. the compo never ended, it just got
 a build system.

 also spotted: DOSBox running on OpenVMS on Alpha. someone out
 there is keeping the faith harder than all of us combined.

